&quot;Leave the gun. Take the cannoli.&quot;



  _____  

From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com [mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com] On Behalf Of
April Abercrombie
Sent: Thursday, May 21, 2009 10:10 AM
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] Re: Ebay auction for sorta Frank&#39;s Box?








You want we should whack &#39;im Frank??



----- Original Message ----- 

From: Frank &lt;mailto:purplealiengirl@...&gt;  Sumption 

To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups &lt;mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com&gt; .com 

Sent: Thursday, May 21, 2009 9:05 AM

Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] Re: Ebay auction for sorta Frank&#39;s Box?



 Same old crap, these self proclaimed experts have no idea what they are
talking about! It&#39;s not the selling of boxes that gets me, it&#39;s the
description of how it works--friggin&#39; clueless! &quot;The Box&quot; does not generate
white noise that allows spirits to create voices, the entities use the bits
of speech, and music to form voices! You&#39;re supposed to believe these people
are &quot;professional investigators&quot;, yet they can&#39;t even get the simplest
concept. When I speak up, I&#39;m the one being mean and negative. 



 &quot;Experts&quot;! forget the tired old way of recording EVP, white noise is not
needed, and is a real pain to listen to. White noise was just an early
attempt to provide a raw audio, in the early days, but it was piss poor at
best! Forget that crap, you need something that provides human speech bits,
and frequencies. Of course you can get direct direct recordings without
noise or raw audio, but---it tends to be weak noise that most of time are
questionable. 



 So just for the record, the box functions by sweeping a radio across it&#39;s
tuning range, the resulting bits of human specch, music and noise is
referred to as raw audio, which the entities rearrange, or re-modualte to
form meaningful messages. EVPmaker provides this raw audio by chopping up
pre-recorded SPEECH, stored as a .wav file, then playing this audio through
the computer speakers while recording the result at the same time. EVPmaker
does not create white noise either.



 Frank-S

On Thu, May 21, 2009 at 8:25 AM, April Abercrombie &lt;april@abercrombiegh
&lt;mailto:april@...&gt; ostresearch.com&gt; wrote:



Ok-found the &quot;Report This Item&quot; link. But there is no option for untrue
advertising. So I guess eBay doesn&#39;t think that is a big enough offense.



Someone could contact the seller and tell him then they know it isn&#39;t true.
I don&#39;t feel qualified to do so since I only know Frank from this list, and
I have only been on this list a short time.



It may not do any good, but maybe it will.





----- Original Message ----- 

From: April Abercrombie &lt;mailto:april@...&gt;  

To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups &lt;mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com&gt; .com 

Sent: Thursday, May 21, 2009 8:09 AM

Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] Re: Ebay auction for sorta Frank&#39;s Box?



Yes...I know.... but it is fun to fantasize. Plus, if I am in a position to
make a difference I will. The problem is knowing when or where that position
is.



----- Original Message ----- 

From: Kristin Morris &lt;mailto:ckmorris95@...&gt;  

To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups &lt;mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com&gt; .com 

Sent: Thursday, May 21, 2009 7:56 AM

Subject: RE: [EVP-ITC] Re: Ebay auction for sorta Frank&#39;s Box?



We can&#39;t police the entire internet.  People should take responsibility for
themselves and do some research and find out how this works before they
purchase.  

Caveat emptor..  


  _____  


From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups &lt;mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com&gt; .com
[mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups &lt;mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com&gt; .com] On Behalf
Of April Abercrombie
Sent: Thursday, May 21, 2009 8:45 AM
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups &lt;mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com&gt; .com
Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] Re: Ebay auction for sorta Frank&#39;s Box?





Exactly! That&#39;s what I&#39;m sayin&#39;.

Wouldn&#39;t it be a hoot if Frank himself blasted the guy. But that isn&#39;t the
mature way..... ;)

----- Original Message ----- 

From: threadsintyme@ &lt;mailto:threadsintyme@...&gt; juno.com 

To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups &lt;mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com&gt; .com 

Sent: Thursday, May 21, 2009 5:52 AM

Subject: RE: [EVP-ITC] Re: Ebay auction for sorta Frank&#39;s Box?

Why don&#39;t some of us respond to his ad...and take serious issue with this
business of his lying to the public about Frank? 

That info is a serious breach of eBay policy. He could be banned from eBay
for life. 
Al
---------- Original Message ----------
From: &quot;Kristin Morris&quot; &lt;ckmorris95@sbcgloba
&lt;mailto:ckmorris95@...&gt; l.net&gt;
To: &lt;EVP-ITC@yahoogroups &lt;mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com&gt; .com&gt;
Subject: RE: [EVP-ITC] Re: Ebay auction for sorta Frank&#39;s Box?
Date: Thu, 21 May 2009 06:16:27 -0500

WOW.. Frank.  I didn&#39;t realize you were charging - and &quot;thousands of
dollars&quot; to boot!  Must be to pay for that Faraday Cage and the white noise
generator thing this yahoo believes are in all your creations.  And hurry
because &quot;his supplier&quot; (cough - cough Radio Shack) is discontinuing!  But no
worries he has &quot;sold over 2 dozen of these &#39;Frank&#39;s Boxes devices&quot; so he
must be legit because he knows - and actual customer bought a &#39;real&#39; Frank&#39;s
Box and said it was equal!  Awesome.

k


  _____  


From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups &lt;mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com&gt; .com
[mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups &lt;mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com&gt; .com] On Behalf
Of ourobouros2k2
Sent: Thursday, May 21, 2009 12:50 AM
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups &lt;mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com&gt; .com
Subject: [EVP-ITC] Re: Ebay auction for sorta Frank&#39;s Box?






Been following this unprofessional idiot&#39;s items for awhile now. I love how
he says that Frank charges thousands of dollars for an original Frank&#39;s box.


This dude is the worst type of con, preying on people who know only enough
to be familiar with the term Frank&#39;s box. Then again, it always has bothered
me when people take shack hacks and charge stupid prices for them on ebay
under the Frank&#39;s box moniker.

This guy is based out of Nevada I believe, and his group&#39;s ethics leave
little to be desired. Takes all kinds, I reckon...

Andy

